author: Inside Edition
description: The Lee County Sheriff's Office in Florida was called to assist some homeowners with an...unusual intruder.
title: Cops Chase Wild Boar #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: The notorious Jeffrey Epstein birthday book featuring a poem apparently signed "Donald Trump" with a sketch of a woman's body is getting attention. The poem is just one of the sleazy birthday messages in the 238-page book put together by Epstein's long time girlfriend Ghislane Maxwell. There are many pages of photographs of Epstein with young women, many half naked. There was also a letter from Bill Clinton praising Epstein's "childlike curiosity." Trump fired back Tuesday.
title: Inside Jeffrey Epstein's Notorious Birthday Book

author: Inside Edition
description: A 35-year-old woman got lost while filming a reality show, YouTube's Survival Games. After the pilot located her, rescuers on the ground knew where to go and made contact. The reality show competition takes place in Michigan on a strip of land 20 miles long. Inside Edition spoke to Amber Tuesday from a train heading back home to California. The producers were thrilled when Amber was found uninjured, but they blame her for getting lost in the first place.
title: Woman Rescued After Getting Lost in Woods Filming Reality Show

author: Inside Edition
description: Two American travelers learned they were on the wrong flight. The travel influencers realized their flight to Nice, France, was actually a flight to Tunis, Tunisia. They tried to deboard but they were out of luck. The commotion caught the attention of fellow passengers. The women say they were in Rome, Italy, and missed their flight to France. When they tried to rebook their flight to Nice, they say the ticket agent apparently heard Tunis, 500 miles from their intended destination.
title: Travel Influencers Realize They Are on Wrong Flight

author: Inside Edition
description: There is growing outrage over the brutal murder of a 23-year-old woman on a commuter train. The accused killer has a history of violence and was free on no-cash bail. Surveillance video shows Ukrainian refugee Iryna Zarutska stepping on to the train after working at a pizza parlor. In the seat behind her was 34-year-old Decarlos Brown. He opened a pocket knife and stabbed Zarutska. The video caught the attention of President Donald Trump.
title: Surveillance Video Shows Fatal Stabbing of Ukrainian Refugee

author: Inside Edition
description: Carol West thought she'd found love online with who she thought was a retired US Army general. The 70-year-old now realizes she was being set up. They communicated several times a day, and soon the alleged scammer started asking her for money. West gave the swindler $60,000, mainly cash mailed to him in padded envelopes. Cops say Cory Woodall was part of a criminal ring targeting vulnerable folks looking for love. West and a Florida sheriff confronted the alleged scammer.
title: 70-Year-Old Romance Scam Victim Confronts Suspect After Losing $60K

author: Inside Edition
description: Court is back in session on "Hot Bench." Inside Edition was behind the scenes of season 12 with judges Rachel Juarez, Yodit Tewolde, and new judge Daniel Mentzer. The show has moved across the country to a brand new sleek and modern courtroom in Connecticut. The show also has a brand new bailiff, Gina Findley, a former police officer and detective. The show still remains the same: three judges, three opinions, one final verdict.
title: Behind the Scenes of 'Hot Bench' New Season

author: Inside Edition
description: Archie Wilson moved from his home in Australia to play football at the University of Nebraska.
title: Family Travels 9,000 Miles to See Son Play College Football #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Authorities say they got a report of a golf cart driving into Atwood Lake in Ohio. Investigators say Ruth Miller, 40, admitted to driving the cart to the lake and throwing her 4-year-old child off the dock, into the water. They say Miller then drove the cart back to her family's camper to pick up her other children, a teenage daughter and 18-year-old twin sons. She then allegedly drove the golf cart into the lake with the children on it. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Amish Mom Admits to Throwing 4-Year-Old in Ohio Lake to 'Give Him to God'

author: Inside Edition
description: Pittsburgh Pirates fan Kavan Markwood spoke exclusively to INSIDE EDITION’s Steven Fabian about his harrowing fall from the nosebleed seats onto the field. Against all odds, Markwood survived—but he broke his back, ribs, neck, and more. Markwood says the incident was just an accident. “I just hope everyone knows that I fell and I didn’t jump over the railing. It was just a tragic accident,” he says.
title: Baseball Fan Who Fell From Bleachers Onto The Field Speaks Out

author: Inside Edition
description: An intrepid feline tried and tried again to travel up a descending escalator at the airport in Istanbul, Turkiye. Cats are known for their quick reflexes and predator instincts. Negotiating moving stairs? Not so much. Fortunately for the cat, a kind human eventually intervened, picking up the feline and putting it on the right track—that is to say, the escalator going up. Hopefully it didn't miss its flight.
title: Cat Tries and Fails to Walk Up Descending Escalator

author: Inside Edition
description: Twenty years after their bitter divorce, Charlie Sheen and Denise Richards hugged on a red carpet.
title: Charlie Sheen and Denise Richards Reunite on Red Carpet #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Florida grandmother Donna Adelson was found guilty of orchestrating the assassination of her daughter's ex-husband, law professor Dan Markel.
title: Grandmother Found Guilty in Ex-Son-in-Law's Hitman Murder #shorts
